* Python utilities to draw plots from the output of any main
  programs. Remember to actually run the main programs before!

* Example usage within the "plots" directory:

  - Higgs inflation:

      python ./fooiplots.py ../src/hi hi slowroll
      python ./fooiplots.py ../src/hi hi powerlaw      	     

  - Spontaneous symmetry breaking 3

      python ./fooiplots.py ../src/ssbi ssbi3 slowroll
      python ./fooiplots.py ../src/ssbi ssbi3 powerlaw

* For more advanced options, check out

      python ./fooiplots.py --help

* You can add contour plot showing one- and two-sigma constraints on
  (ns,logr) and (sr2,sr1) by providing the contour files, which
  defaults to (edit fooiplots.py)

     data/contour_sr2_sr1_level_0.dat
     data/contour_sr2_sr1_level_1.dat

  and 

     data/contour_ns_logr_level_0.dat	
     data/contour_ns_logr_level_0.dat

  This files can be generated from GetDist samples by using the module
  "aspicdist.py".

    T
    
